<module>
    <h>taigh</h>
    <p><g>taigh</g>
        <en>a house</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
            noun</a>.</p>

    <p>Examples of <g>taigh</g> as the subject of the predicative verb <a href="?gd=bi"
            ><g>bi</g></a> – <ul>
            <li>non-specified – <ul>
                    <li>with attributive adjective – <xl>
                            <li>
                                <gd>Dé tha air a’ chnoc? Tha taigh mór air a’ chnoc.</gd>
                                <tr>What is on the hill? There is a big house on the hill.</tr>
                                <ref text="617">td. 20</ref>
                            </li>
                        </xl>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>an taigh</g>
                        <en>the house</en> – <ul>
                            <li>attributive adjective – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Càit a bheil an taigh mór? Tha an taigh mór air a’ chnoc
                                            àrd.</gd>
                                        <tr>Where is the big house? The big house is on the tall
                                            hill.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [229]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

    <p>Examples of <g>taigh</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=an^preposition"
                ><g>an</g></a>
        <en>in</en> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>anns an taigh</g>
                        <en>in the house</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha Seònaid anns an taigh.</gd>
                                        <tr>Janet is in the house.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14</ref>
                                    </li>
                                    <!--<li>
                                        <gd>A bheil an cat anns an taigh còmhla ri Seònaid?</gd>
                                        <tr>Is the cat in the house with Janet?</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 15 [227]</ref>
                                    </li>-->
                                    <!--<li>
                                        <gd>Dé tha a’ chaileag a’ dèanamh anns an taigh?</gd>
                                        <tr>What is the girl doing in the house?</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [adapted]</ref>
                                    </li>-->
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Cha robh sinn a’ cluich anns an taigh.</gd>
                                        <tr>We were not playing in the house.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 21 [230]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <p>Examples of <g>taigh</g> as the complement of the preposition <a href="?gd=aig"
            ><g>aig</g></a>
        <en>at</en> – <ul>
            <li>pre-specified – <ul>
                    <li>definite article – <g>aig an taigh</g>
                        <en>at the house, at home</en> – <ul>
                            <li>unmodified – <xl>
                                    <li>
                                        <gd>Tha Seònaid aig an taigh.</gd>
                                        <tr>Janet is at home.</tr>
                                        <ref text="617">td. 14 [227]</ref>
                                    </li>
                                </xl>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>

</module>
